    <h1>About PlainCompare</h1>
    <p>PlainCompare is a free tool that lets you compare U.S. metro areas and states side by side across seven key dimensions:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living</strong> — Regional Price Parities from the Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA)</li>
      <li><strong>Rent</strong> — HUD Fair Market Rents for studios through 4-bedroom units</li>
      <li><strong>Crime</strong> — FBI Uniform Crime Report violent and property crime rates</li>
      <li><strong>Wages</strong> — Bureau of Labor Statistics occupational salary data</li>
      <li><strong>Schools</strong> — NCES enrollment, student-teacher ratios, and charter school data</li>
      <li><strong>Childcare</strong> — Department of Labor childcare cost estimates</li>
      <li><strong>Environment</strong> — EPA facility counts, water systems, and Superfund sites</li>
    </ol>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>Select two cities or states using the comparison tool on the homepage. PlainCompare queries seven separate government databases in real time and presents the results in a clear, side-by-side format with winner highlights.</p>
    <h2>Data Sources</h2>
    <p>All data comes from official U.S. government sources. PlainCompare is not affiliated with any government agency. Data is provided as-is for informational purposes only.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>PlainCompare is part of the <a href="https://kiznis.studio">Kiznis Studio</a> network of public data portals.</p>
  </section>
</Base>
